    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What does Cove make besides dishwashers?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Nothing. Cove is a single-product brand — the dishwasher is the entire product line. Two models only: the DW2450 stainless and the DW2450WS panel-ready. Cove is the third brand in the Sub-Zero Group alongside Sub-Zero (refrigeration) and Wolf (cooking). Each brand stays in one category and engineers at specialist depth. For integrated Sub-Zero/Wolf/Cove kitchens in LA luxury homes, we service all three brands in a single visit."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What does error code 050187 mean on my Cove DW2450?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Water flow fault — the dishwasher isn't receiving the expected water flow during fill. Per Cove's OEM service documentation, first step is a 30-second breaker reset: turn off the home circuit breaker for 30 seconds, turn back on, retest. Clears about 25% of 050187 codes as a transient fault. Persistent 050187 after reset: verify the water supply stopcock is open, check the inlet hose for kinks, clean the water inlet filter (mesh at the inlet connection), verify water pressure is in spec (20-80 psi). If all external paths are fine, the inlet valve itself has failed. We carry DW2450 water inlet valves on the truck. A related code 050186 is the same family of water-flow faults with slightly different trigger conditions."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "My Cove shows 050135 — what's wrong?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "050135 is a fault-level error indicating the wash pump motor (MOT1) drew more than 2.54 amps, indicating overload or seizure. Per Cove's service manual, diagnostic sequence: confirm the wash pump wire harness connections are tight and have electrical continuity, including across connector PJ26; inspect the pump impeller for debris or glass shards that may be causing mechanical bind; test the pump motor windings for continuity and resistance (should read 4-8 ohms). Common cause: glass shard from a broken wine glass made it past the filters into the pump. Clearing the debris free; pump replacement if motor windings are damaged ($485-$680). We diagnose on the first visit."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I enter Service Mode on my Cove?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The Cove DW2450 service mode is accessible via a specific button sequence: touch and hold the Auto key AND the Heavy key simultaneously for 5 seconds, release the Heavy key, then continue to hold the Auto key for another 5 seconds. 'Service Mode' appears on the UIM. From Service Mode, a technician can review user settings and offsets, monitor unit performance metrics, and manually activate/deactivate individual components for testing. To exit Service Mode, touch and hold the Cancel key. This is intended for trained service technicians — most owners don't need to access it. We use Service Mode during every Cove diagnostic to read full error history rather than just the current active code."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does Cove dishwasher repair cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Diagnostic is $89, waived with repair. Typical Cove DW2450 repairs: water inlet valve $245-$345, wash pump (MOT1) replacement $485-$680, drain pump $285-$385, air break assembly $145-$215, door gasket $185-$265, door latch $195-$285, heater (post-TCO rework units) $345-$485, thermal cutoff (TCO) $95-$145, coarse filter $45 flat, fine filter $55 flat, MCM (main control module) $620-$880, UIM (user interface module) $385-$540, circulation pump impeller $165-$240. Labor and parts quoted before work starts."
