  <!-- ── FAQ ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">FAQ</p>
      <h2>Cove dishwasher repair — common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>What does Cove make besides dishwashers?</summary>
        <p>Nothing. One product line, two models (DW2450 stainless, DW2450WS panel-ready). Cove is the dishwasher brand inside the Sub-Zero Group alongside Sub-Zero (refrigeration) and Wolf (cooking). Each brand stays in one category.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>050187 water flow error</summary>
        <p>Water flow fault. 30-second breaker reset clears 25% as transient. Persistent: check supply valve, inlet filter, hose kinks, water pressure (20-80 psi). If externals OK, inlet valve failed ($245-$345). We carry on the truck.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>050135 wash pump overload</summary>
        <p>MOT1 drew >2.54A — mechanical bind. Check PJ26 connector, inspect impeller for debris (glass shards common in entertaining kitchens), test motor windings 4-8 ohms. Debris clearance free; pump $485-$680 if windings damaged.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How do I enter Service Mode?</summary>
        <p>Touch+hold Auto AND Heavy keys simultaneously 5 seconds, release Heavy, hold Auto another 5 seconds. "Service Mode" appears on UIM. Review settings, monitor performance, test components. Exit: touch+hold Cancel. We use on every diagnostic.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Dishwasher won't drain</summary>
        <p>Diagnostic: clean coarse ($45) + fine ($55) filters first, check drain hose for kinks, verify garbage disposal not blocked, test drain pump ($285-$385). Manual drain via Service Mode + hold Auto.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Dishwasher won't start</summary>
        <p>Four causes: door not closed within 4-second Start timer, Child Lock/Sabbath/Showroom mode active, Delayed Start programmed, breaker tripped. If none fit, door latch ($195-$285) or UIM ($385-$540). We check settings before parts.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Are you Factory Certified?</summary>
        <p>No — factory-trained but independent. Inside 2-year warranty, call Sub-Zero Group 800-222-7820 for Factory Certified dispatch at no parts cost. Post-warranty: faster response, lower labor rate. Matched Sub-Zero + Wolf + Cove = one dispatch.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
